== VIM Buffers ==

A Vim buffer is a file loaded into memory for editing.

=== Buffer commands ===

 :buffers      ... list buffers
 :ls

 :bN           ... switch to buffer N
 :Nb
 N Ctrl-^

 Ctrl-^        ... toggle between last and current buffer

 :bd [N]       ... remove buffer N from list of buffers
 :[M,N]bd      ... remove buffers m to N from list of buffers

 :edit .       ... open the file browser
 :e.

 :Explore      ... open the file browser in directory of current file
 :E

=== File browser navigation ===

Navigate in file browser like in a "normal" VIM session:

 Use h j k l / to move
 <CR> to select a file or directory

 -       ... move directory up 
 %       ... create a new file
 d       ... create a new directory
 D       ... delete a file or directry
 R       ... rename a file or directory


